{id:"course1",emoji:"🎬",title:"28-Day Course: AI Video Production",color:"#f0a500",badge:"NEW",lessons:[ 
{title:"Day 1 — Welcome & Your Video Stack",body:"WELCOME TO YOUR 28-DAY AI VIDEO PRODUCTION COURSE\n\nBy the end of this course you will have a complete video production system running. One that Becky manages and that produces professional videos every single day.\n\nYOUR COMPLETE FREE STACK:\n• ElevenLabs — Professional voiceover ($5/month)\n• Wan2.2 — AI video scene generation (FREE)\n• FFmpeg — Video merging server (FREE — FreeStack)\n• CapCut — Captions and final polish (FREE)\n• YouTube OAuth — Direct publishing (FREE)\n\nTOTAL COST: $5/month\n\nTHIS IS YOUR WAN2.2 FACTORY:\nStep 1: Write script → ElevenLabs generates audio\nStep 2: Break script into scenes → Wan2.2 generates each scene\nStep 3: FFmpeg merges audio + scenes into one video\nStep 4: CapCut adds captions and final touches\nStep 5: Publish direct to YouTube\n\nYOUR CAST:\n• Lisa — News anchor (black blazer) — Fri + Sat affiliate promos\n• Susan — Authority expert (navy blazer) — Monday\n• Paul — Trusted grandfather (overalls/beard) — Thursday\n• Alisha — Charismatic host (blue top/glasses) — Wednesday\n• Becky Host (gold blouse) + Becky Guest (white blouse) — Affiliate shows\n\nDAY 1 ACTION: Read this lesson twice. Know your stack cold."}, 
{title:"Day 2 — ElevenLabs Voiceover Mastery",body:"ELEVENLABS — YOUR PROFESSIONAL VOICE ENGINE\n\nElevenLabs turns your scripts into broadcast-quality voiceovers in seconds.\n\nSETUP:\n1. Go to elevenlabs.io\n2. Sign up — $5/month Starter plan\n3. Go to Voice Library — browse 3000+ voices\n4. Find voices that match each anchor:\n • Lisa: Professional, clear, authoritative female\n • Susan: Warm, friendly, trustworthy female\n • Paul: Deep, steady, grandfather male\n • Alisha: Energetic, charismatic, sales female\n • Becky: Polished, professional female\n\nWORKFLOW:\n1. Write your script in Hub Engine V4\n2. Copy to ElevenLabs → Speech Synthesis\n3. Select your anchor voice\n4. Set stability: 0.75 | Similarity: 0.85\n5. Generate → Download MP3\n6. This MP3 goes into Step 3 (FFmpeg)\n\nPRO TIP: Create a custom voice clone for each anchor for maximum consistency. ElevenLabs lets you clone a voice from just 1 minute of audio."}, 
{title:"Day 3 — Wan2.2 Scene Prompting",body:"WAN2.2 — YOUR FREE AI VIDEO GENERATOR\n\nWan2.2 generates cinematic video scenes from text prompts. It is completely free through open source.\n\nHOW IT WORKS:\nYou write a scene description → Wan2.2 generates a 3-5 second video clip → You chain clips together with FFmpeg.\n\nSCENE PROMPT FORMULA:\n[SHOT TYPE] [SUBJECT] [ACTION] [SETTING] [LIGHTING] [MOOD]\n\nEXAMPLE FOR LISA NEWS ANCHOR:\nMedium close-up professional Asian female news anchor speaking directly to camera, modern TV news studio, clean background with blue accent lighting, authoritative professional atmosphere, broadcast quality\n\nEXAMPLE FOR PAUL GRANDFATHER:\nMedium shot trusted elderly male grandfather sitting in comfortable chair, warm home setting, soft natural window lighting, reassuring grandfatherly atmosphere, authentic documentary style\n\nEXAMPLE FOR B-ROLL:\nAerial drone shot modern city skyline at golden hour, glowing windows, light traffic, cinematic widescreen, professional documentary style\n\nDAY 3 ACTION:\nWrite 5 scene prompts for your next Lisa Friday video using this formula."}, 
{title:"Day 4 — The Becky Video Workflow",body:"BECKY IS YOUR VIDEO PRODUCTION MANAGER\n\nBecky (your AI agent) manages the complete Wan2.2 Factory so you do not have to do each step manually.\n\nBECKY'S COMPLETE VIDEO WORKFLOW:\n\nYou say to Becky: 'Produce a 60-second affiliate promo for Vidnoz with Lisa as anchor.'\n\nBecky does:\n1. SCRIPT — Writes the full anchor script (60 seconds = ~150 words)\n2. ELEVENLABS — Generates the voice prompt for Lisa's voice\n3. WAN2.2 SCENES — Writes 8-12 scene prompts matching the script beats\n4. FFMPEG — Provides the merge command to combine audio + scenes\n5. CAPCUT — Lists caption style and any final edits needed\n6. YOUTUBE — Writes title, description, tags, and thumbnail text\n\nYOU JUST RUN THE STEPS.\nBecky does the thinking. You do the clicking.\n\nUSE BECKY IN THE BECKY TAB above to start a video production right now."}, 
{title:"Day 5 — Google Stitch for Thumbnails",body:"GOOGLE STITCH — FREE AI UI & THUMBNAIL DESIGNER\n\nGoogle Stitch (stitch.withgoogle.com) is your free AI design tool for thumbnails, landing pages, and promo graphics.\n\nFOR VIDEO THUMBNAILS:\nGo to stitch.withgoogle.com\nPrompt: Design a YouTube thumbnail for a video titled '[YOUR TITLE]'. High contrast. Bold text. Professional news style. Include a shocked/curious face expression area. Colors: black and gold.\n\nFOR AFFILIATE LANDING PAGES:\nPrompt: Design a landing page for [PRODUCT] affiliate offer. Hero section with bold headline about saving time. 3 benefit bullets. Email capture form. CTA button in gold. Dark professional design.\n\nNEW AT GOOGLE I/O 2026:\n• Continuous streaming — design updates in real time as you type\n• Multiplayer editing — collaborate simultaneously\n• Direct Netlify publish — goes live with one click\n• design.md — brand consistency across all AI tools\n\nDAY 5 ACTION: Go to stitch.withgoogle.com and design a thumbnail for your next Lisa video."}, 
{title:"Day 6 — FFmpeg Video Merging",body:"FFMPEG — YOUR FREE VIDEO MERGE ENGINE\n\nFFmpeg combines your ElevenLabs audio + Wan2.2 scenes into one complete video. FreeStack Video hosts your FFmpeg server for free.\n\nBASIC MERGE COMMAND:\nffmpeg -i scene1.mp4 -i scene2.mp4 -i scene3.mp4 \\\n-i voiceover.mp3 -filter_complex \\\n'[0:v][1:v][2:v]concat=n=3:v=1:a=0[outv]' \\\n-map '[outv]' -map 3:a output.mp4\n\nBECKY GENERATES THIS FOR YOU.\nYou never need to write FFmpeg commands manually. Just tell Becky the scene count and she writes the exact command.\n\nFREESTACK VIDEO SETUP:\n1. Your FFmpeg server runs on FreeStack (no cost, no watermark)\n2. Upload your scenes and audio\n3. Run Becky's merge command\n4. Download your finished video\n5. No monthly fee, no watermark\n\nDAY 6 ACTION: Have Becky write an FFmpeg command for a 4-scene Lisa video."}, 
{title:"Day 7 — CapCut Captions & Final Polish",body:"CAPCUT — YOUR FREE CAPTION AND POLISH TOOL\n\nCapCut adds professional auto-captions and final visual polish to your Wan2.2 videos.\n\nCAPTION WORKFLOW:\n1. Import your FFmpeg-merged video into CapCut\n2. Click Auto Captions → Generate\n3. Select font: Bold, high contrast (white text, black outline)\n4. Review and correct any errors\n5. Add your logo in bottom corner\n6. Export at 1080p\n\nPRO CAPTION SETTINGS:\n• Font: Bold sans-serif (Impact or similar)\n• Size: Large enough to read on phone\n• Color: White with black stroke\n• Position: Lower third\n• Style: Word-by-word highlight (karaoke style)\n\nFOR SHORTS AND REELS: Export 9:16 vertical\nFOR YOUTUBE: Export 16:9 horizontal\n\nCOMPLETE CHECKLIST:\n[ ] Captions accurate and readable\n[ ] Logo watermark added\n[ ] Correct aspect ratio for platform\n[ ] Audio levels balanced\n[ ] First 3 seconds have strong hook\n[ ] CTA visible at end\n\nDAY 7 = END OF WEEK 1. You now know your complete video stack."}, 
{title:"Day 8-14 — Weekly Production Schedule",body:"YOUR WEEKLY VIDEO PRODUCTION SCHEDULE\n\nMONDAY — SUSAN'S SHOW\nTopic: Business/lifestyle/how-to content\nLength: 60-90 seconds\nStyle: Warm, conversational, helpful\nBecky workflow: Susan authority expert script\nPost to: YouTube + LinkedIn\n\nWEDNESDAY — ALISHA'S SHOW\nTopic: AI tools, product promos, high energy\nLength: 45-60 seconds\nStyle: Charismatic, persuasive, sales energy\nBecky workflow: Alisha promo script\nPost to: TikTok + Instagram + YouTube\n\nTHURSDAY — PAUL'S SHOW\nTopic: Breaking news, bold claims, trust content\nLength: 30-45 seconds\nStyle: Short punchy sentences, grandfather authority\nBecky workflow: Paul breaking news script\nPost to: YouTube + Facebook\n\nFRIDAY — LISA'S SHOW\nTopic: Tech news, AI developments, serious analysis\nLength: 60 seconds\nStyle: CNN-style, authoritative, fact-based\nBecky workflow: Lisa news anchor script\nPost to: YouTube + LinkedIn + Twitter\n\nSATURDAY — LISA AFFILIATE PROMO\nTopic: Affiliate product promotion\nLength: 45 seconds\nStyle: Credible endorsement\nBecky workflow: Lisa affiliate promo script\nPost to: All platforms with affiliate link\n\nBECKY + BECKY — AFFILIATE SHOW\nSchedule: As needed\nFormat: Host interviews Guest about AI tool\nBecky workflow: Full interview script format"}, 
{title:"Day 15-21 — Scaling Your Output",body:"WEEK 3 — SCALING TO DAILY VIDEOS\n\nBy now your Wan2.2 Factory is running smoothly. Week 3 is about scaling output without scaling effort.\n\nBATCH PRODUCTION METHOD:\nInstead of making 1 video per day — make 5 on Monday.\n\nBATCH WORKFLOW:\n1. Monday morning: Write all 5 scripts in Hub Engine\n2. ElevenLabs: Generate all 5 voiceovers in one session\n3. Wan2.2: Generate all scene batches together\n4. FFmpeg: Merge all 5 videos\n5. CapCut: Add captions to all 5\n6. Schedule posts throughout the week\n\nTIME SAVED: 4 hours of daily work becomes 2 hours on Monday.\n\nFREE LLM API FOR SCALE:\nUse Free LLM API (localhost:3001/v1) to run scripts through multiple AI models simultaneously:\n• Gemini 2.5 Flash — fast script drafts\n• Groq Llama — fast iteration\n• GitHub GPT-4o — quality polish\n800 million free tokens per month combined.\n\nBATCH SCRIPT PROMPT TO BECKY:\n'Write 5 scripts for this week: Monday=Susan on [topic], Wednesday=Alisha on [topic], Thursday=Paul on [topic], Friday=Lisa on [topic], Saturday=Lisa affiliate for [product]'"}, 
{title:"Day 22-28 — Monetization & Growth",body:"WEEK 4 — TURNING VIDEOS INTO INCOME\n\nYOUR 5 AFFILIATE PROGRAMS:\n\n1. VIDNOZ — 50% Commission\nEvery Lisa Saturday video ends with Vidnoz affiliate link\nTarget: 10 sales/month = $250 passive income\n\n2. INVIDEO — 30% Commission\nEvery Alisha Wednesday features InVideo\nTarget: 15 sales/month = $200 passive income\n\n3. MAILERLITE — $140 Per Referral\nSusan Monday builds email list content\nTarget: 3 referrals/month = $420 passive income\n\n4. CAPCUT — Revenue Share\nPaul Thursday mentions CapCut for free editing\nTarget: 20 referrals/month = varies\n\n5. UDEMY — 15% Per Course\nHost/Guest Becky show reviews AI courses\nTarget: 10 sales/month = $75 passive income\n\nMONTH 1 TARGET: $500 affiliate income\nMONTH 3 TARGET: $1,500 affiliate income\nMONTH 6 TARGET: $3,000+ affiliate income\n\nLOCAL BUSINESS VIDEO SERVICE:\nStarter: $200/month (4 videos)\nProfessional: $400/month (8 videos)\nPremium: $700/month (daily videos)\nTarget: 3 local clients = $600-$2,100/month additional\n\nTOTAL POTENTIAL MONTH 6: $3,000-$5,000/month"} 
]}, 
