{id:"video",emoji:"🎥",title:"Video Production Deep Dive",color:"#f0a500",lessons:[ 
{title:"Complete Becky Video Workflow",body:"BECKY IS YOUR FULL VIDEO PRODUCTION MANAGER\n\nBecky does the entire Wan2.2 Factory for you from one prompt.\n\nTELL BECKY IN THE BECKY TAB:\n'Produce a full 60-second affiliate video for Vidnoz with Lisa as anchor for this Friday.'\n\nBECKY DELIVERS:\n\n1. SCRIPT (150 words, 60 seconds)\nComplete word-for-word anchor script with timing marks.\n\n2. ELEVENLABS PROMPT\nExact settings: Voice profile, stability, similarity boost, style.\n\n3. WAN2.2 SCENE PROMPTS (8-10 scenes)\nEach scene described in detail: shot type, subject, setting, lighting, mood.\n\n4. FFMPEG MERGE COMMAND\nExact command to merge all scenes + audio into final video.\n\n5. CAPCUT INSTRUCTIONS\nCaption style, font, color, placement, any text overlays needed.\n\n6. YOUTUBE PACKAGE\nTitle (5 options), description with affiliate links, 30 hashtags in 3 tiers, thumbnail text.\n\nONE PROMPT. FULL VIDEO PACKAGE.\nThat is Becky's power."}, 
{title:"Wan2.2 Advanced Scene Prompts",body:"ADVANCED WAN2.2 PROMPTING FOR PROFESSIONAL RESULTS\n\nSHOT TYPES:\n• ECU (Extreme Close-Up): Eyes, product detail\n• CU (Close-Up): Face, anchor talking head\n• MCU (Medium Close-Up): Chest up, standard anchor shot\n• MS (Medium Shot): Waist up, product demos\n• WS (Wide Shot): Full scene, establishing shots\n\nLIGHTING TERMS:\n• Rembrandt lighting — dramatic, authoritative (Paul, Lisa)\n• Soft box lighting — warm, approachable (Susan, Alisha)\n• Natural window light — authentic, documentary\n• Studio three-point — professional broadcast\n\nPRO ANCHOR PROMPTS:\n\nLISA (News):\n'MCU professional East Asian female news anchor mid-30s, speaking directly to camera, modern broadcast news studio, blue accent lighting, authoritative CNN-style atmosphere, 4K broadcast quality'\n\nSUSAN (Authority):\n'MCU professional White female expert 38-40, warm confident presentation, clean office setting with books and plants, soft natural lighting, trustworthy documentary style'\n\nPAUL (Grandfather):\n'MS White male grandfather 60s, seated in leather chair, warm study setting, soft lamp lighting, reassuring trustworthy atmosphere, authentic family documentary'\n\nALISHA (Charismatic):\n'MCU Latina female host 40s, energetic warm smile, bright modern studio, vibrant lighting, dynamic sales presentation energy, influencer production quality'"}, 
{title:"Google Stitch for Video Assets",body:"GOOGLE STITCH — BUILD VIDEO ASSETS IN MINUTES\n\nGo to: stitch.withgoogle.com (completely free)\n\nFOR YOUTUBE THUMBNAILS:\nPrompt: 'Create a YouTube thumbnail for a video titled [YOUR TITLE]. Shocked/curious face expression placeholder. Bold text overlay. High contrast black and gold color scheme. Professional news broadcast style. 1280x720px.'\n\nFOR LOWER THIRDS (name tags in video):\nPrompt: 'Design a lower third name tag graphic for a news broadcast. Name: Lisa Chen. Title: AI Technology Reporter. Style: modern CNN-style. Dark background with gold accent line.'\n\nFOR INTRO SCREENS:\nPrompt: 'Design a 3-second news broadcast intro screen for AffiliateMediaHub Studio. Channel logo area. Gold and black color scheme. Professional broadcast typography.'\n\nFOR AFFILIATE LANDING PAGES:\nPrompt: 'Design a high-converting landing page for Vidnoz AI affiliate offer. Hero: Save 6 hours of video editing per week. Three benefits. Email capture. Gold CTA button. Dark professional theme.'\nThen click Export → Publish to Netlify. LIVE in seconds.\n\nDESIGN.MD BRAND FILE:\nCreate one design.md file with your brand colors (black, gold #f0a500), fonts (Space Grotesk, DM Sans), and spacing rules. Every Stitch page you generate automatically matches your brand."}, 
{title:"Your Video Distribution System",body:"PUBLISH ONCE — DISTRIBUTE EVERYWHERE\n\nYour Wan2.2 Factory produces one master video. Then you distribute it across every platform automatically.\n\nYOUR DISTRIBUTION STACK:\n\nYOUTUBE (via YouTube OAuth):\n• Long form: 60-90 second videos\n• Shorts: Vertical 9:16 version\n• Becky writes: Title, description, tags, chapter markers\n\nFACEBOOK:\n• Upload the same video directly\n• Becky writes platform-specific caption\n• 5 relevant hashtags only (Facebook hates over-hashtagging)\n\nINSTAGRAM REELS:\n• Vertical crop of same video\n• Becky writes: Hook caption + 20 hashtags\n• First line must be your strongest hook\n\nTIKTOK:\n• Same vertical version\n• Becky writes: Short punchy caption + trending sounds suggestion\n• Best posting time: 7-9am or 7-9pm your timezone\n\nLINKEDIN:\n• Horizontal version for professional audience\n• Becky writes: Professional insights angle\n• Focus on business value not entertainment\n\nTHE MATH:\n1 video produced = 5 platform posts = 5x reach for same effort\n\nBECKY PROMPT: 'Write platform-specific captions for a video about [TOPIC] for all 5 platforms: YouTube, Facebook, Instagram, TikTok, LinkedIn. Include hashtags for each.'"} 
]}, 
{id:"prompt",emoji:"⚡",title:"Prompt Engineering 101",color:"#a78bfa",lessons:[ 
{title:"What Is A Prompt",body:"A PROMPT is simply the instruction you give to an AI.\n\nThe quality of what you get back depends 100% on the quality of what you put in.\n\nBAD PROMPT: Write a script\n\nGOOD PROMPT: Write a 45-second news script for Lisa, my professional Asian news anchor, about AI replacing warehouse jobs. Tone: urgent and authoritative. Strong hook in first 3 seconds. End with a call to action to visit our website.\n\nThe good prompt tells the AI:\n- WHO is delivering it (Lisa)\n- WHAT the topic is\n- HOW LONG (45 seconds)\n- WHAT TONE (urgent, authoritative)\n- WHAT STRUCTURE (hook + CTA)\n\nTHAT IS ALL PROMPT ENGINEERING IS. Being specific and clear.\n\nREMEMBER THE FORMULA: RTFCS\nRole + Task + Format + Constraints + Style"}, 
{title:"The 5-Part Prompt Formula",body:"RTFCS — YOUR MASTER PROMPT FORMULA\n\n1. ROLE — Tell the AI who to be\n'You are a professional TV news writer for AffiliateMediaHub Studio'\n\n2. TASK — Tell it exactly what to do\n'Write a 45-second anchor script for Lisa'\n\n3. FORMAT — Tell it how to structure it\n'Divide into HOOK, BODY, CTA with second markers'\n\n4. CONSTRAINTS — Give it limits\n'Under 100 words. No jargon. No filler phrases.'\n\n5. STYLE — Tell it the tone\n'Urgent and authoritative like CNN Breaking News'\n\nFULL EXAMPLE:\n'You are a professional TV news writer for AffiliateMediaHub Studio. Write a 45-second anchor script for Lisa about AI replacing warehouse jobs. Divide into HOOK, BODY, CTA with second markers. Under 100 words, no jargon. Tone: urgent and authoritative like CNN Breaking News.'\n\nTHAT is a world-class prompt. Use Becky tab to run it now."}, 
{title:"10 Power Prompts For Your Studio",body:"COPY AND USE THESE RIGHT NOW IN BECKY TAB:\n\n1. LISA NEWS SCRIPT:\nWrite a 60-second news script for Lisa, professional Asian news anchor, about [TOPIC]. Hook in first 3 seconds. CNN-style authority. End with CTA.\n\n2. ALISHA AFFILIATE PROMO:\nWrite a 45-second affiliate promo for Alisha about [PRODUCT]. Hook: time wasted before finding this. High energy, persuasive, include FOMO. Affiliate CTA at end.\n\n3. SUSAN TUTORIAL:\nWrite a 60-second tutorial script for Susan about [TOPIC]. Warm conversational tone. Start with relatable story. Three clear steps. Helpful CTA.\n\n4. PAUL BREAKING NEWS:\nWrite a 30-second breaking news script for Paul. Topic: [TOPIC]. Maximum 8 words per sentence. Bold and direct. Grandfather authority. Strong close.\n\n5. BECKY INTERVIEW:\nWrite a 90-second Host/Guest interview for Becky reviewing [AI TOOL]. Becky Host asks 3 questions. Becky Guest gives expert answers. Include affiliate recommendation at end.\n\n6. WAN2.2 SCENES:\nWrite 8 detailed Wan2.2 scene prompts for a 60-second [ANCHOR] video about [TOPIC]. Each prompt: shot type, subject description, setting, lighting, mood. Professional broadcast quality.\n\n7. YOUTUBE PACKAGE:\nWrite a complete YouTube package for a video titled [TITLE]: 5 title options, 200-word description with affiliate links, 30 hashtags in 3 tiers, thumbnail text.\n\n8. EMAIL SEQUENCE:\nWrite a 3-email affiliate sequence for [PRODUCT]. Day 1: the problem. Day 2: the solution. Day 3: special offer. Each under 200 words. [ANCHOR NAME] voice.\n\n9. SOCIAL CAPTIONS:\nWrite captions for all 5 platforms for a video about [TOPIC]: YouTube, Facebook, Instagram TikTok, LinkedIn. Platform-specific length and style.\n\n10. LOCAL BUSINESS PITCH:\nWrite a 60-second verbal sales pitch for a local business in [CITY] to sell them a $400/month video service. Name the problem. Show the solution. Reduce risk with free trial offer."} 
]}, 
{id:"affiliate",emoji:"💰",title:"Affiliate Marketing Mastery",color:"#10b981",lessons:[ 
{title:"Your 5 Programs Overview",body:"YOUR 5 ACTIVE AFFILIATE PROGRAMS\n\nVIDNOZ — 50% Commission — TOP EARNER\nSign up: vidnoz.com/affiliate\nBest anchor: Alisha (energy) or Lisa (credibility)\nBest content: Tutorial showing video creation in 10 minutes\nConversion angle: Creates professional videos without a camera\n\nINVIDEO — 30% Commission\nSign up: invideo.io/affiliate\nBest anchor: Alisha or Paul\nBest content: 15-second affiliate ad templates\nConversion angle: News-style ads for local businesses\n\nMAILERLITE — $140 Per Referral\nSign up: mailerlite.com/referral\nBest anchor: Susan (warm, trustworthy)\nBest content: Email list building tutorials\nConversion angle: Build your list, earn $140 per referral\n\nCAPCUT — Revenue Share\nSign up: capcut.com/affiliate\nBest anchor: Lisa or Alisha\nBest content: Short-form video editing tutorials\nConversion angle: Free professional editing for Reels and TikTok\n\nUDEMY — 15% Per Course\nSign up: udemy.com/affiliate\nBest anchor: Susan or Paul\nBest content: Course reviews and learning recaps\nConversion angle: Skills that pay in the AI economy"}, 
{title:"Affiliate Content Calendar",body:"MONTHLY AFFILIATE CONTENT CALENDAR\n\nWEEK 1 — VIDNOZ FOCUS\nMon Susan: 'How I manage my video production schedule'\nWed Alisha: 'Vidnoz tutorial — 10 minutes to professional video' (PROMO)\nThu Paul: 'Why businesses need weekly video in 2026'\nFri Lisa: 'AI video tools changing small business marketing'\nSat Lisa: 'Vidnoz affiliate promo — try free link below'\n\nWEEK 2 — INVIDEO FOCUS\nMon Susan: 'Creating a content calendar that actually works'\nWed Alisha: 'InVideo affiliate ad templates — quick tutorial' (PROMO)\nThu Paul: 'The video tool that replaced my editing team'\nFri Lisa: 'InVideo vs traditional video production: the numbers'\nSat Lisa: 'InVideo affiliate promo — 30% off link below'\n\nWEEK 3 — MAILERLITE FOCUS\nMon Susan: 'Why your email list is worth more than your social following'\nWed Alisha: 'How I built a 1,000 subscriber email list in 30 days'\nThu Paul: 'The asset nobody talks about: your email list'\nFri Lisa: 'MailerLite review: free email marketing for small business'\nSat Lisa: 'Get MailerLite free — earn $140 for each referral'\n\nWEEK 4 — CAPCUT & UDEMY\nRotate: CapCut editing tutorials and Udemy course reviews\n\nBECKY PROMPT: 'Build me a complete 4-week affiliate content calendar with scripts for all 5 anchors using this rotation schedule.'"} 
]}, 
{id:"anchors",emoji:"🎭",title:"Your 4 Anchors + Becky",color:"#e879f9",lessons:[ 
{title:"Complete Anchor Guide",body:"YOUR 5 ANCHORS — COMPLETE REFERENCE\n\nLISA — Lead News Anchor\nAppearance: Professional Asian female, mid-30s, black blazer\nSchedule: Friday show + Saturday affiliate promo\nShows: Podcast (with Susan)\nBest for: Tech news, AI developments, serious analysis, credible endorsements\nVoice: Authoritative, CNN-style, fact-based\nElevenLabs voice: Professional female, high clarity\nWan2.2 style: MCU, studio lighting, news broadcast quality\n\nSUSAN — Authority Expert\nAppearance: Professional female, navy blazer\nSchedule: Monday show\nShows: Podcast (with Lisa), Business Show (with Alisha)\nBest for: Business content, lifestyle, how-to, trustworthy tutorials\nVoice: Warm, credible, knowledgeable\nElevenLabs voice: Warm professional female\nWan2.2 style: MCU/MS, natural lighting, expert setting\n\nPAUL — Trusted Grandfather\nAppearance: Male, overalls/beard, grandfather energy\nSchedule: Thursday show\nShows: Podcast 2 (with Alisha)\nBest for: Breaking news, bold claims, trust content, urgent topics\nVoice: Deep, steady, authoritative, grandfather warmth\nElevenLabs voice: Deep mature male, steady pace\nWan2.2 style: MS, warm home setting, soft lamp lighting\n\nALISHA — Charismatic Host\nAppearance: Female, blue top, glasses\nSchedule: Wednesday show\nShows: Podcast 2 (with Paul), Business (with Susan)\nBest for: Affiliate promos, product launches, sales content, high energy\nVoice: Energetic, persuasive, charismatic, FOMO-driven\nElevenLabs voice: Energetic female, upbeat pace\nWan2.2 style: MCU, bright studio, dynamic energy\n\nBECKY HOST + BECKY GUEST — Affiliate Show\nAppearance: Host=gold blouse | Guest=white blouse\nSchedule: As needed for affiliate content\nFormat: Interview style — Host interviews Guest about AI tool\nBest for: Affiliate product deep dives, tool reviews, recommendations\nKey: Guest is the 'expert' who discovered the tool. Host is the interviewer."}, 
{title:"Show Teams & Schedules",body:"YOUR 4 SHOW FORMATS\n\nPODCAST (Lisa + Susan)\nDay: Varies (Lisa Fri / Susan Mon content feeds this)\nFormat: Professional news discussion\nTopics: AI news, business technology, digital trends\nLength: 60-90 seconds\nAffiliate integration: Natural mention in discussion\n\nPODCAST 2 (Paul + Alisha)\nDay: Thu/Wed content feeds this\nFormat: Grandfather wisdom meets modern energy\nTopics: Business lessons, AI tools for non-techies\nLength: 60-90 seconds\nAffiliate integration: Paul endorses, Alisha promotes\n\nBUSINESS SHOW (Alisha + Susan)\nDay: Wed/Mon content\nFormat: Business insights and tools\nTopics: Entrepreneurship, AI business tools, local business\nLength: 60-90 seconds\nAffiliate integration: Susan recommends, Alisha closes\n\nAFFILIATE SHOW (Becky Host + Becky Guest)\nDay: As needed\nFormat: Product discovery interview\nTopics: Specific AI tool or affiliate product\nLength: 90-120 seconds\nAffiliate integration: Core content — both Beckys love the tool\n\nBECKY PROMPT FOR ANY SHOW:\n'Write a [SHOW NAME] episode script for [ANCHOR 1] and [ANCHOR 2] about [TOPIC]. [LENGTH] seconds. Include natural affiliate mention for [PRODUCT] with CTA at end.'"} 
]}, 
{id:"tools",emoji:"🛠",title:"New AI Tools 2026",color:"#06b6d4",badge:"NEW",lessons:[ 
{title:"Google Stitch — Free AI Designer",body:"GOOGLE STITCH — YOUR FREE AI DESIGN TOOL\nURL: stitch.withgoogle.com\n\nWHAT IT DOES:\nType a description in plain English → Stitch builds a complete website, landing page, or app UI in real time. You steer it while it builds.\n\nGOOGLE I/O 2026 UPDATES (May 20):\n• Continuous streaming — renders UI as you type, not after\n• Real-time multiplayer editing (free — multiple people at once)\n• Direct Netlify publish — goes live with one click, no developer needed\n• design.md — your brand colors/fonts lock in across all pages\n\nFOR YOUR STUDIO — USE CASES:\n1. Affiliate landing pages (Lisa/Alisha promos)\n2. YouTube thumbnails and channel art\n3. Email opt-in pages for MailerLite list building\n4. Local business promo pages\n5. Hub Engine style pages for clients\n\nGET STARTED IN 5 MINUTES:\n1. Go to stitch.withgoogle.com\n2. Type: 'Design a landing page for [YOUR AFFILIATE PRODUCT]. Dark background, gold buttons, professional news style. Email capture form. 3 benefits. CTA button.'\n3. Watch it build in real time\n4. Click Export → Netlify → LIVE\n\nFREE. No subscription. No watermark."}, 
{title:"Free LLM API — 800M Free Tokens",body:"FREE LLM API — RUN 14 AI PROVIDERS FREE\nURL: github.com/NousResearch/free-llm-api\n\nWHAT IT DOES:\nSelf-hosted proxy that stacks 14 free AI provider tiers behind one OpenAI-compatible endpoint. Auto-failover between providers.\n\nFREE PROVIDERS INCLUDED:\n• Google Gemini 2.5 Flash (best quality)\n• Groq Llama 3.3 70B (fastest speed)\n• GitHub GPT-4o (free with GitHub account)\n• Cerebras (ultra fast)\n• Nvidia (strong models)\n• Mistral (European AI)\n• HuggingFace (100+ models)\n• + 7 more\n\nTOTAL FREE TOKENS: ~800 million/month\n\nSETUP (Windows):\n1. Install Node.js v20+ from nodejs.org\n2. Install Git from git-scm.com\n3. Clone the repo and npm install\n4. Set up .env with encryption key\n5. npm run dev → dashboard at localhost:5173\n\nADD FREE KEYS:\n• Google: aistudio.google.com → Get API Key\n• Groq: console.groq.com → API Keys\n• GitHub: Settings → Developer → Access Tokens\n\nFALLBACK CHAIN:\nGemini 2.5 → Groq → GitHub → rest\nAuto-skips rate-limited providers. Resets midnight UTC.\n\nPOINT ANY APP AT: localhost:3001/v1\nYour Agent OS, Hermes, and Hub Engine all use this for free."}, 
{title:"Agent OS — Multi-Agent Command",body:"AGENT OS — 6 AGENTS RUNNING SIMULTANEOUSLY\n\nYour Agent OS Multi-Agent Command Center runs 6 specialized AI agents at the same time.\n\nYOUR 6 AGENTS:\n• Content Agent — Scripts, copy, SEO, affiliate content\n• Video Agent — Wan2.2 prompts, ElevenLabs, FFmpeg commands\n• Research Agent — Trends, competitor analysis, affiliate research\n• Email Agent — Outreach, sequences, follow-ups\n• Social Agent — YouTube titles, TikTok hooks, LinkedIn posts\n• Strategy Agent — Planning, roadmaps, business growth\n\nBROADCAST FEATURE:\nType one task → hit ALL → all 6 agents work simultaneously\nExample: 'Plan our Vidnoz affiliate campaign for next month'\n→ Content Agent: writes the scripts\n→ Video Agent: plans the Wan2.2 production\n→ Research Agent: finds Vidnoz competitor data\n→ Email Agent: writes the email sequence\n→ Social Agent: writes all captions\n→ Strategy Agent: builds the 4-week plan\n\nAll 6 done in under 90 seconds.\n\nACCESS YOUR AGENT OS:\nDownload the Multi-Agent Command Center HTML file\nOpen in any browser — works immediately\nAdd API key in Settings (Claude or Groq key accepted)\nHit LAUNCH ALL AGENTS"}, 
{title:"Hermes Agent Hub — Local Autonomy",body:"HERMES AGENT HUB — AUTONOMOUS TASK MANAGER\nURL: github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent\n\nWHAT IT IS:\nHermes is an open-source agent app that runs autonomously on your local computer. It manages tasks, builds skills, and runs workflows on a schedule — while you sleep.\n\nKEY FEATURES:\n• Kanban board — manage agent tasks visually\n• Skills system — reusable workflow templates\n• Goal mode — give it a goal, it runs start to finish\n• Schedule timers — runs tasks automatically at set times\n• Saves outputs to your workspace\n• Reads your memory vault/Obsidian\n\nSETUP FOR YOUR STUDIO:\n1. Open Terminal on your laptop\n2. Run Hermes installer\n3. When it asks for API key: paste your GROQ key (gsk_...)\n4. Select model: llama-3.3-70b-versatile\n5. Press Enter through remaining setup\n\nONCE RUNNING — SET THESE GOALS:\n• 'Every Monday: Generate Susan's script for this week'\n• 'Every Wednesday: Generate Alisha's script'\n• 'Every Friday: Generate Lisa's news script and affiliate promo'\n• 'Weekly: Research top 5 AI tool stories for this week'\n\nHermes runs these automatically. You review and approve. Done.\n\nYOUR HERMES AGENT HUB is live on your GitHub at:\nAffiliateMediaHub-Studio/hermes-agent-hub"}, 
{title:"NotebookLM — Research Engine",body:"NOTEBOOKLM — YOUR FREE RESEARCH BRAIN\nURL: notebooklm.google.com\n\nWHAT IT DOES:\nUpload any source (PDF, YouTube URL, article, audio). NotebookLM reads it and lets you chat with the content, generate summaries, audio podcasts, video overviews, and slide decks.\n\nPOWERED BY: Gemini 3 with Deep Research\n\nFOR AFFILIATEMEDIAHUB STUDIO:\n\n1. RESEARCH NOTEBOOKS:\nCreate one notebook per affiliate product\nUpload: Product website, reviews, competitor comparisons\nAsk: 'What are the 5 strongest benefits I should highlight?'\n\n2. COMPETITOR RESEARCH:\nUpload competitor YouTube transcripts\nAsk: 'What topics are they covering that I am not?'\n\n3. AUDIO OVERVIEW TOOL:\nUpload your script → Click Audio Overview\nNotebookLM creates a podcast-style audio discussion of your content\n\n4. SLIDE DECK GENERATOR:\nUpload any research → Click Slides\nComplete slide deck in seconds\n\nCONNECT TO AGENT OS:\nUse the community MCP server for NotebookLM\nClaude can then: open notebooks, add sources, trigger outputs, pull results to your gallery\nAll from one command in your Agent OS chat\n\nSETUP TIP: Use a dedicated Google account for the MCP connection (keeps your main Google account clean)."} 
]}, 
{id:"business",emoji:"💼",title:"Local Business Sales System",color:"#fb923c",lessons:[ 
{title:"Your 60-Second Sales Pitch",body:"SAY THIS TO LOCAL BUSINESSES IN SOUTHEAST TEXAS:\n\n'Hi, my name is John Lanter. I run an AI media production company here in Southeast Texas. I create professional promotional videos for local businesses using AI technology — completely automatically.\n\nEach video gets posted to your social media every single week. No cameras, no film crews, no editing on your end. Just a clean professional video every week that keeps your customers engaged and brings in new ones.\n\nI use the same AI technology that national news studios use. My videos look network-quality and I produce them in minutes.\n\nI can show you a sample right now on my phone. Would you have 2 minutes to take a look?'\n\nTHEN SHOW YOUR BEST LISA OR ALISHA SAMPLE VIDEO.\n\nIf they like it — you have a client.\n\nFOLLOW-UP CLOSE:\n'What I would like to do is create 2 videos completely free for your business — no commitment, no credit card. You keep them either way. If you love them we talk about a simple monthly package. Does that sound fair?'\n\nNOBODY SAYS NO TO FREE."}, 
{title:"Pricing Your Video Service",body:"YOUR SERVICE PACKAGES\n\nSTARTER — $200/month\n• 4 videos per month\n• One platform (YouTube or Facebook)\n• Standard anchor (Susan or Alisha)\n• Script review by client\n\nPROFESSIONAL — $400/month\n• 8 videos per month\n• Two platforms with platform-specific captions\n• Custom anchor selection\n• Client-approved scripts\n• Monthly performance report\n\nPREMIUM — $700/month\n• Daily videos (20+ per month)\n• All 5 platforms\n• Multiple anchors\n• Custom brand avatar option\n• Weekly strategy call\n• Priority turnaround\n\nFIRST CLIENT CLOSE OFFER:\n'Let me create 2 videos completely FREE — no commitment. If you love them, the Starter package is $200/month. That is $50 per video. What does one new customer cost you to acquire? Usually much more than $50.'\n\nBUSINESSES THAT BUY FIRST:\n• Restaurants (before/after hours promos)\n• Real estate agents (listing videos)\n• Gyms and fitness studios\n• Automotive dealerships\n• Medical and dental practices\n• Insurance agents\n• Any retail with foot traffic\n\nSOUTHEAST TEXAS TARGETS:\nOrange, Beaumont, Port Arthur, Bridge City, Vidor, Groves"}, 
{title:"Handling Objections",body:"OBJECTION HANDLING — WHAT TO SAY\n\nI CANNOT AFFORD IT:\n'That is exactly why I offer the free trial. Two videos at zero cost. Once you see the results, the investment pays for itself with one new customer. What does one new customer worth to your business? Let me show you a sample right now.'\n\nWE ALREADY HAVE SOMEONE FOR SOCIAL MEDIA:\n'Video is the number one driver of engagement on every platform right now — Facebook, Instagram, TikTok. I am not replacing what you have — I am adding professional video every week. Most social media managers love having video delivered to them ready to post.'\n\nI NEED TO THINK ABOUT IT:\n'While you think about it — let me create one sample video for your business completely free this week. Can I get your business name and logo? You keep the video no matter what you decide.'\n\nHOW DO I KNOW THIS ACTUALLY WORKS:\n'Businesses using weekly professional video see on average 3x more engagement and 40% more website traffic from social. But you do not have to take my word for it — let me show the sample I made for [similar business nearby].'\n\nI HAD A BAD EXPERIENCE WITH SOCIAL MEDIA BEFORE:\n'I understand. The difference with my system is you see the video and approve it before it ever gets posted. You have complete control and you are never charged until you are happy with the product.'"} 
